 -- Florian Best <best@univention.de>  Thu, 07 Mar 2013 08:17:52 +0100

univention-management-console-module-appcenter (2.0.131-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Bug #30663: If an application requires an extension of the LDAP schema,
    the corresponding packages are installed remotely by the local App Center.
    If the Apache web server is restarted on that remote host during the app
    installation, this does no longer lead to an error message on the local
    App Center.
  * Bug #30172: Improved the confirmation dialog before installing an app by
    listing also packages that will be updated via automatic errata updates
    and all package changes that will be done on remote hosts.

 -- Dirk Wiesenthal <wiesenthal@univention.de>  Wed, 06 Mar 2013 18:27:22 +0100

univention-management-console-module-appcenter (2.0.130-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * set ucr variable repository/app_center/server in postinst; Bug #30264

 -- Florian Best <best@univention.de>  Tue, 05 Mar 2013 12:13:35 +0100

univention-management-console-module-appcenter (2.0.129-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Bug #30637: If only the schema extension for an app was installed and a
    newer version was available, the App Center showed the option to upgrade
    the complete application. This option is now only shown on the server that
    has installed the "core" of the application.

 -- Dirk Wiesenthal <wiesenthal@univention.de>  Mon, 04 Mar 2013 12:24:12 +0100

